['393.                                  \xa0                     LEVI                      SOLOMON                                                                                                          was indicted for                                                          feloniously being found at large before the expirationSee original\xa0 of the term for which he had been ordered to be transported            , April 10th                  .', 'The record of his conviction and order to be transported were produced and read.', ' \xa0                  JOHN                   GODFREY                                                                                        sworn.', 'I took the prisoner at large on the 10th of this month, with a flat of butter on his head, which he had stole out of a waggon.', ' \xa0                  THOMAS                   WITHERS                                                                                        sworn.', 'I took the prisoner on the 11th of October, for stealing goods from Mr. Dunford, of which he was convicted; I was at the trial; I am certain the prisoner is the man; I knew him before.', ' \xa0                  NATHAN                   LYONS                                                                                        sworn.', 'I was at the taking of the prisoner on the 11th of October; he was tried for stealing pins the 21st of October, and was convicted.', "PRISONER's DEFENCE.", "I had his Majesty's free pardon to go for a soldier; I was in the Savoy.", 'GODFREY. He did not receive a pardon, there was nine of them broke away from the ship together.', '                                                      GUILTY            .                                                          Death            .', 'Tried by the First London Jury before Mr. RECORDER.']